nt check and deposit it in the bank.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"data":{}}]}}}]}]}]}]}},"nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Processing float","marks":[{"type":"bold"}]}],"object":"inline","type":"key-term","ref":"7a418240-ea73-4df3-ad66-8a55a53df908"},{"object":"text","text":": The time it takes the firm to process a customer’s payment check and deposit it in the bank.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"f874959e-a7f6-42b8-844c-c13512834406","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"493cb25c-542c-4c8f-bd41-a3bf303cc4a0","nodes":[{"data":{"ref":"39e0fca7-d036-4740-9826-4119ee2351f7","stage":{"ref":"7bd818f8-f5c1-4b18-8f0e-d067c59a2f36","sections":[{"ref":"c4149aaa-33f7-4baa-b22d-cbfa373da72b","rows":[{"ref":"bd02f652-74d9-438a-b6fd-28a563ed0ec1","columns":[{"ref":"2e619313-63e5-40ff-8553-fe550deab50b","stageElements":[{"ref":"fc0a209b-d53c-4637-b065-540ab0e3475c","type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"button","ref":"17f6f560-505b-424a-8b1b-402e3e922e7c","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"d867587e-2d04-4578-bdb0-f79ca4e54369","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"The time it takes a bank to give a firm credit for customer payments the firm has deposited in the bank.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"data":{}}]}}}]}]}]}]}},"nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Availability float","marks":[{"type":"bold"}]}],"object":"inline","type":"key-term","ref":"200d2013-d686-446c-81ff-05eb536db14f"},{"object":"text","text":": The time it takes a bank to post the funds from customer payments the firm has deposited in the bank.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}]}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"9c643afa-a412-48bb-9623-73b468624618"},{"type":"stage-element-image","config":{"url":{"$ambrosia":"aero:asset:upload","urn":"urn:aero:d087b0b0-44e0-11ed-82a0-5b736ba8ac7f","asset":{"urn":"urn:aero:d087b0b0-44e0-11ed-82a0-5b736ba8ac7f","asset":{"assetProvider":"ALFRESCO","id":"d087b0b0-44e0-11ed-82a0-5b736ba8ac7f","assetMediaType":"image","assetVisibility":"GLOBAL","ownerId":"e88133a0-8dc4-11eb-964e-4d7e264c9958","subscriptionId":"f0afd4d0-d2ff-11ea-9998-d57e1e28aca1","alfrescoId":"2c563120-ad21-41ed-aa7c-2ceb08018d8a","name":"FG_19_002.jpg","version":"2.0","lastModifiedDate":1664998392,"lastSyncDate":1665085927},"source":{"small":{"width":2741,"url":"https://assets-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/d087b0b0-44e0-11ed-82a0-5b736ba8ac7f/small/bd5adbcb78f73e645a382cf11faee1a5.jpeg","height":300},"original":{"width":5483,"url":"https://assets-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/d087b0b0-44e0-11ed-82a0-5b736ba8ac7f/medium/bd5adbcb78f73e645a382cf11faee1a5.jpeg","height":600},"medium":{"width":5483,"url":"https://assets-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/d087b0b0-44e0-11ed-82a0-5b736ba8ac7f/medium/bd5adbcb78f73e645a382cf11faee1a5.jpeg","height":600},"thumb":{"width":1371,"url":"https://assets-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/d087b0b0-44e0-11ed-82a0-5b736ba8ac7f/thumb/bd5adbcb78f73e645a382cf11faee1a5.jpeg","height":150}},"metadata":{"altText":"","workURN":"","caption":"","alfrescoPath":"bronte-e2e-testing-qaint/documentLibrary/BV E2E Test/[10-05-2022] Berk","originalAssetName":"FG_19_002.jpg","longDesc":"","height":"88"}}},"alt":"","caption":"","layout":{"captionPosition":"Below"},"credit":"","activityLabel":"Figure 19.2","activityTitle":"Collection Float"},"height":88,"ref":"2dd206d7-eb92-41fd-887f-9f38c1658a34"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"heading-three","ref":"209afc00-fa4d-422e-a266-a8cead432171","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Disbursement Float","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"fa317c6b-e512-41d5-9014-7e504051c641"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"7b4420c0-d82d-43dd-bee6-8bf0e48959a6","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"The time it takes before payments to suppliers actually result in a cash outflow for the firm is referred to as ","marks":[]},{"data":{"ref":"8f76df92-0f21-49af-8bbb-024d0fca031b","stage":{"ref":"40af07df-87f8-421d-860b-77c17b344325","sections":[{"ref":"afe4f7ba-9e11-4a70-86f3-a3e252321a5a","rows":[{"ref":"4a08bd49-007b-480f-93b3-6d21c51cbbc6","columns":[{"ref":"f93ac070-f159-4bd8-9e3b-af1404286a97","stageElements":[{"ref":"532d5157-0175-4435-8b51-bd7776dab27b","type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"button","ref":"111e0d4f-49a6-4920-b697-290a1b5e337e","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"db6ef1ae-3014-43c3-ae1b-685ab329a0e6","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"The time it takes before a firm’s payments to its suppliers actually result in a cash outflow for the firm.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"data":{}}]}}}]}]}]}]}},"nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"disbursement float","marks":[{"type":"bold"}]}],"object":"inline","type":"key-term","ref":"1cac707a-b04c-4319-ab29-e955b9484dce"},{"object":"text","text":". Similar to collection float, it is a function of mail time, processing time, and check-clearing time. Although a firm may try to extend its disbursement float in order to lengthen its payables and reduce its working capital needs, it risks making late payments to suppliers. In such a case, the firm may be charged an additional fee for paying late or may be required to pay cash before delivery (CBD) or cash on delivery (COD) for future purchases. In some cases, the supplier may refuse to do business in the future with the delinquent firm.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"500739cd-c7c8-45b7-b851-5890d77eb9e7"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"heading-three","ref":"5b1d69f5-1b49-4ee7-afb2-0dc3149039e9","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Electronic Check Processing","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"b4431777-9b4d-466d-ba95-c6a59b97d949"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"23331752-aac7-4e8c-8c2f-44d609771b30","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Firms can employ several methods to reduce their collection and disbursement floats. The ","marks":[]},{"data":{"ref":"c892a304-912b-4c74-b426-fced63cb32a2","stage":{"ref":"55c0dc7f-091f-40e5-9cb6-d6785de1cd4f","sections":[{"ref":"6e0d0ec4-b788-428c-a5a9-cc8d8e273639","rows":[{"ref":"c81a4acf-7961-47cf-b8f8-b062165bbfda","columns":[{"ref":"cb37750e-19a5-4fe8-a6df-f6b9cb43d547","stageElements":[{"ref":"20559978-162e-420f-8d6f-f4fd56aee501","type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"button","ref":"1bf2fa54-fa45-4ba3-b3ef-41b5932702b3","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"4ac2a419-638d-493b-b9a1-533a07d11a4f","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Eliminates the disbursement float due to the check-clearing process. Banks can process check information electronically and, in most cases, the funds are deducted from a firm’s checking account on the same day that the firm’s supplier deposits the check in its bank.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"data":{}}]}}}]}]}]}]}},"nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Check Clearing for the 21st Century Act (Check 21)","marks":[{"type":"bold"}]}],"object":"inline","type":"key-term","ref":"64e764b2-11e3-4827-acd2-bed9bbe50b2d"},{"object":"text","text":", which became effective on October 28, 2004, eliminated the part of the disbursement float due to the check-clearing process. Under the act, banks can process check information electronically and, in most cases, the funds are deducted from a firm’s checking account on the same day the firm’s supplier deposits the check in its bank. Unfortunately, even though the funds are taken out of the check writer’s account almost immediately under Check 21, the check recipient’s account is not credited as quickly. As a result, the act does not serve to reduce collection float.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"0e4d0863-db98-41bb-a6e6-d90deeeb8c8b"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"4d7f593a-ee1c-4d2a-8539-397fedc57905","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"There are, however, several ways that a firm ","marks":[]},{"object":"text","text":"can","marks":[{"type":"italic"}]},{"object":"text","text":" reduce its collection float. For example, the firm may streamline its in-house check-processing procedures. In addition, with electronic collection, funds are automatically transferred from the customer’s bank account to the firm’s bank account on the payment date, reducing the collection float to zero. The methods a firm employs to reduce its collection float are not without costs, of course. New check-processing systems could be expensive and disruptive, and hiring a collection agency to speed up collections generates costs such as fees to the agency as well as bad will with the firm’s customers. Therefore, to decide which method, if any, to employ, the firm must compare the costs and benefits of systems that allow it to use its cash for a longer period.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"29cbdabe-f421-45d1-882f-6bb15d20af79"}]}]}]},{"cssClass":"aside-group Sidebar_1Aside","rows":[{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"heading-two","ref":"f43f3a5a-dd81-40ef-8951-5889dee97353","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Concept Check","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"e591c1a1-959a-4bc7-bb79-445b8268cfec"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"1","startValue":3},"ref":"e0901ea1-f8d7-4aba-8f74-cfe052b229bf","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"d05c18b7-fe1a-4dee-846f-e683bd8adc45","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"a310be08-c1dc-4666-b8cc-56b352322ec2","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"What does the term “2/10, net 30” mean?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"ddff4240-5556-4850-baca-760ca8f6fc28","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"99242a76-dc66-4083-8b8c-118f30d2e596","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"List three factors that determine collection float.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}]}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"1e36fedf-82cc-4321-8d54-152a883e4b79"}]}]}]}]},"screenType":"","transitions":{"enter":{"animation":"","duration":0,"easing":"","customKeyframes":""},"exit":{"animation":"","duration":0,"easing":"","customKeyframes":""}},"lockElements":false,"learnerCurrentAttempt":1,"footer":{"buttonText":"Next","buttonIcon":"Arrow","showFooter":false,"showHistoryNavButtons":false,"previewFooter":false,"position":"Fixed to screen bottom","footerComponent":{"showFooterDropArea":"hide","width":100,"footerComponentsAlignment":"right"}},"styles":{"background":{},"stage":{"maxWidth":940,"background":"rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)","responsive":true,"padding":{"vertical":60,"horizontal":60},"border":{"color":"rgba(224, 224, 224, 1)","radius":0,"width":0}},"elements":{"padding":{"vertical":10,"horizontal":10}},"footer":{"buttonColor":"rgba(0, 115, 202, 1)","textColor":"rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7)","backgroundColor":"rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)","padding":10,"corners":4,"border":"none","shadow":"0 -1px 4px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.06), 0 0 12px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.1)"},"feedback":{"width":320,"textColor":"rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7)","backgroundColor":"rgba(255, 